	</form></div><span class="pb doctop" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0054">54<a style="padding-left: 5px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-16/ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0054.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a></span><div class="doc">
      
      <h1>From L. de Chavannes de la Giraudire</h1>
      <div class="docbody">
        <div class="opener">
          <table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Monsieur</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Amsterdam ce 23 fevrier 1784</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
        </div>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Le politique Hollandais est mort, et le Mercure Hollandais vient reprendre sa place. Jai lhonneur denvoyer  Votre Excellence le premier N<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">o</span> de cette feuille nouvelle. Vous pourrez vous procurer les suivantes chez les Libraires de la Haie qui dbitent le Courrier van Europa. Jespere que le public naura pas  regretter M. Cerisier pour le zele et le patriotisme, mais moi je regretterai bien fort que Votre Excellence ne se trouve plus  Amsterdam pour y recevoir vos instructions.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Je vous prie de vouloir me faire passer tout ce qui pourra concerner lAmrique, et trouver place dans un papier public. Le Chantre de lAmrique a quelque droit me semble  dfendre les intrts des Treize Etats-Unis, et il doit le premier-tre instruit aprs Votre
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0055">[55<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-16/ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0055.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
Excellence de ce quil veut savoir au public en ce pays, avant mme la Gazette de Leyde, tout patriote et bien ententionne quelle soit.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Mon adresse, pour tout ce qui peut concerner le Mercure Hollandais, est  lAuteur de cette feuille chez Holtrop Libraire dans le Kalvestraat.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Jattends toujours la rponse  ma derniere lettre,<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0003" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> et suis avec le dvoment et le respect que vous me connaissez, / Monsieur / De Votre Excellence / Le trs-humble, trs-obissant Serviteur</p>
        <div class="closer">
          <p class="signed">De Chavannes de la Giraudiere</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="translation">
        <h2>TRANSLATION</h2>
        <div class="opener">
          <table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Amsterdam, 23 February 1784</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
        </div>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Le politique hollandais</span> is dead, and the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Mercure hollandais</span> has taken its place. I have the honor of sending to your excellency the first issue of this new leaf. You can buy the subsequent issues from the booksellers at The Hague who sell the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Courier de lEurope.</span> I hope the public will not miss Mr. Cerisiers zeal and patriotism, but as for me I will greatly miss your excellencys being in Amsterdam so I can receive your instructions there.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">I beseech you to send me all that concerns America and would fit in a public paper. The <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Chantre de lAmrique</span> has some right, it seems to me, to defend the interests of the thirteen United States, and it must be the first after your excellency to be informed about what the public wants to know in this country, even before the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Gazette de Leyde,</span> as patriotic and well intentioned as it may be.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">My address in all matters concerning the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Mercure hollandais</span> is in care of the author of this publication at the Holtrop bookseller on Kalvestraat.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">I am still awaiting a reply to my last letter,<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0003" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> and remain with the devotion and respect that you know in me, sir, your excellencys very humble &amp; very obedient servant</p>
        <div class="closer">
          <p class="signed">De Chavannes de la Giraudiere</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="docback">
        <div class="note-source" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0035-sn">
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Manuscripts and other materials, 16391889, in the Adams Manuscript Trust collection given to the Massachusetts Historical Society in 1956 and enlarged by a few additions of family papers since then. Citations in the present edition are simply by date of the original document if the original is in the main chronological series of the Papers and therefore readily found in the microfilm edition of the Adams Papers (see below).&lt;/expan&gt; ]">Adams Papers</span>).</p>

        </div>
        <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0001-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0001">1</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">The last extant issue of <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Le politique hollandais</span> is of 12 Jan. 1784. Antoine Marie Cerisiers role as the papers editor, however, likely ended much earlier, with the issue of 11 Aug. 1783, the result of his struggle over control of the journal with the papers publisher, Amsterdam bookseller Jacobus Adrianus Crajenschot (vol. <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-14-02-0195#ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0300" class="pageNo">14:300301</a>). Crajenschots assumption of control is evident from the notice appearing at the end of the 18 Aug. issue: J. A. Crajenschot, Editeur &amp; seul propritaire de cette feuille; and the signed Lettre du Libraire, Editeur &amp; Propritaire de cette Feuille  ses Confreres that appeared in the issue of 25 August. That letter denied Cerisiers claim to be sole editor and declared that Crajenschots role had been at least as important, if not more so. Cerisiers ouster as editor may explain his 3 Sept. 1783 letter to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> requesting his assistance in obtaining a position in the French foreign ministry (vol. <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-15-02-0112%20ADMS-print-06-15-02-0113#ADMS-06-15-02-pb-0244" class="pageNo">15:244245</a>). Nothing is known of the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Mercure hollandais</span> beyond what Chavannes de la Giraudire says in this letter, and the copy sent to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> has not been found.</p>

        </div>

        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0002-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0002">2</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">The reference to <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Chantre de lAmrique</span> remains obscure, but that to the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Gazette de Leyde,</span> edited by Jean Luzac, is of some interest. Until the latter part of 1781, Luzacs <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Gazette</span> had been <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s principal means for
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0056">[56<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-16/ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0056.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
disseminating news from and about America. That role ended only when <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> sought the wider audience offered by the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Gazette dAmsterdam</span> and <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Le politique hollandais.</span> For Luzacs complaint about <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s shift to other papers, see vol. <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-12-02-0083%20ADMS-print-06-12-02-0084#ADMS-06-12-02-pb-0125" class="pageNo">12:125127</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-12-02-0085-0002%20ADMS-print-06-12-02-0086%20ADMS-print-06-12-02-0087#ADMS-06-12-02-pb-0128" class="pageNo">128130</a>. It is also worthy of note that C. W. F. Dumas obtained a position for Cerisier with the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Gazette de Leyde</span> (from Cerisier, 10 Aug. 1786, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Boston Public Library ]">MB</span>).</p>

        </div>

        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0003-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0035-fn-0003">3</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Having learned from <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> of the land office that Joseph Ward had opened in Boston (vol. <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-15-02-0172%20ADMS-print-06-15-02-0173#ADMS-06-15-02-pb-0350" class="pageNo">15:350352</a>), Chavannes de la Giraudire wrote on 26 Jan. 1784 to propose opening a branch in Europe and to ask for assistance in setting up a partnership with Ward and his associates (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Manuscripts and other materials, 16391889, in the Adams Manuscript Trust collection given to the Massachusetts Historical Society in 1956 and enlarged by a few additions of family papers since then. Citations in the present edition are simply by date of the original document if the original is in the main chronological series of the Papers and therefore readily found in the microfilm edition of the Adams Papers (see below).&lt;/expan&gt; ]">Adams Papers</span>). In his reply of 30 Jan. (<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ letterbook copy (Letterbook copies are normally unsigned, but any such copy is assumed to be in the hand of the person responsible for the text unless it is otherwise described.) ]">LbC</abbr>, <span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Formerly, Adams Papers, Microfilms. The corpus of the Adams Papers, 16391889, as published on microfilm by the Massachusetts Historical Society, 19541959, in 608 reels. Cited in the present work, when necessary, by reel number. Available in research libraries throughout the United States and in a few libraries in Canada, Europe, and New Zealand.&lt;/expan&gt; ]">APM</span> Reel 107), <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> enclosed a copy of Wards brochure but declared that he could give no more aid to such a private venture. In his reply of 4 March (<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ letterbook copy (Letterbook copies are normally unsigned, but any such copy is assumed to be in the hand of the person responsible for the text unless it is otherwise described.) ]">LbC</abbr>, <span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Formerly, Adams Papers, Microfilms. The corpus of the Adams Papers, 16391889, as published on microfilm by the Massachusetts Historical Society, 19541959, in 608 reels. Cited in the present work, when necessary, by reel number. Available in research libraries throughout the United States and in a few libraries in Canada, Europe, and New Zealand.&lt;/expan&gt; ]">APM</span> Reel 107), <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> referred to his earlier letter and repeated that he was unable to help further. By the time Chavannes de la Giraudire wrote again, on 9 Aug. (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Manuscripts and other materials, 16391889, in the Adams Manuscript Trust collection given to the Massachusetts Historical Society in 1956 and enlarged by a few additions of family papers since then. Citations in the present edition are simply by date of the original document if the original is in the main chronological series of the Papers and therefore readily found in the microfilm edition of the Adams Papers (see below).&lt;/expan&gt; ]">Adams Papers</span>), he was residing in Amsterdam and intended to move to the United States. Having been promised land in Virginia and passage across the Atlantic, he sought from <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> money and letters of recommendation. In a last letter to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, dated 23 Sept. (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Manuscripts and other materials, 16391889, in the Adams Manuscript Trust collection given to the Massachusetts Historical Society in 1956 and enlarged by a few additions of family papers since then. Citations in the present edition are simply by date of the original document if the original is in the main chronological series of the Papers and therefore readily found in the microfilm edition of the Adams Papers (see below).&lt;/expan&gt; ]">Adams Papers</span>), Chavannes de la Giraudire reported that he and his family had been stranded in Amsterdam after the vessel that was to carry them to the United States had been seized by the owners creditors, and he expressed his resolve to take his children to London and seek free passage across the ocean there. <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> apparently made no reply to either of these later letters. For a full account of Chavannes de la Giraudires flight from France and removal to the United States, see his <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-04-05-02-0235" class="document">letter to George Washington of 10 July 1787</a> in <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Papers of George Washington: Confederation Series,&lt;/i&gt; ed. W. W. Abbot and others, Charlottesville, Va., 19921997; 6 vols. ]">Washington, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Papers, Confederation Series,</span></span> 5:252256.</p>

        </div>

